üìñ The Story of Rib

The Rib flows through the Upper Lea (Hertfordshire) catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 10 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 4,555 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 528 identified species and 220 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Rib shows moderate diversity compared to other rivers in the study (#7 of 10). The river supports 16 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Water vole, Water shrew) and invasive species requiring management attention.
